article.headline: Butler 64, Cleveland St. 55
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Willie Veasley scored 16 points and Shelvin Mack added 15 to lead Butler to a 64-55 win over Cleveland State on Thursday night. The Bulldogs (13-4, 6-0 Horizon) remained undefeated at home this season. They scored half their points inside the paint, and put in 20 off of turnovers. Veasley's scoring tied a career best he set almost a year ago, also against Cleveland State. This time around, it was his highest-scoring showing of the season. Ronald Nored also tied his own career best with 11 points, a mark he likewise set last year against Cleveland State. Jeremy Montgomery led the game in scoring with 22 points for the Vikings (7-11, 3-3) while Trevon Harmon added 12 and Norris Cole finished with 11.
